1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,025
We said next July,

2
00:00:07,175 --> 00:00:09,201
same lake, same week,

3
00:00:09,351 --> 00:00:11,376
same bags on the bunks,

4
00:00:11,526 --> 00:00:13,551
same dumb no-sleep.

5
00:00:13,701 --> 00:00:15,726
Same camp map,

6
00:00:15,876 --> 00:00:17,902
same mess hall line,

7
00:00:18,052 --> 00:00:20,077
same names on the list,

8
00:00:20,227 --> 00:00:22,252
just not this time.

9
00:00:22,402 --> 00:00:24,427
You said, “I’m still me,”

10
00:00:24,577 --> 00:00:26,603
I said, “I know,”

11
00:00:26,753 --> 00:00:28,778
but the form says girl,

12
00:00:28,928 --> 00:00:30,953
and the answer’s no.

13
00:00:31,103 --> 00:00:33,128
So the same old place

14
00:00:33,278 --> 00:00:35,304
where we always went

15
00:00:35,454 --> 00:00:37,479
is still taking girls,

16
00:00:37,629 --> 00:00:39,654
but the girls all went.

17
00:00:39,804 --> 00:00:41,829
You were my friend,

18
00:00:41,979 --> 00:00:44,005
and you’re my friend,

19
00:00:44,155 --> 00:00:46,180
and he’s my friend

20
00:00:46,330 --> 00:00:48,355
who was she back then.

21
00:00:48,505 --> 00:00:50,530
And I know that’s wrong,

22
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:52,706
or the wrong way round,

23
00:00:52,856 --> 00:00:54,881
but my mouth gets lost

24
00:00:55,031 --> 00:00:57,056
where my thoughts get found.

25
00:00:57,206 --> 00:00:59,231
If she’s he and he’s still you,

26
00:00:59,381 --> 00:01:01,407
and you’re still you but the rule says
“who,”

27
00:01:01,557 --> 00:01:03,582
how’s a girls’ camp a girls’ camp

28
00:01:03,732 --> 00:01:05,757
when the girls aren’t there?

29
00:01:05,907 --> 00:01:07,932
If we said we’d go like we always do,

30
00:01:08,082 --> 00:01:10,108
and I still mean me and I still mean you,

31
00:01:10,258 --> 00:01:12,283
why’s the same same place

32
00:01:12,433 --> 00:01:14,458
suddenly somewhere?

33
00:01:14,608 --> 00:01:16,634
I can still see us

34
00:01:16,784 --> 00:01:18,809
by the dock at dusk,

35
00:01:18,959 --> 00:01:20,984
trading ghost stories,

36
00:01:21,134 --> 00:01:23,159
trading clothes for luck.

37
00:01:23,309 --> 00:01:25,335
You in that hoodie,

38
00:01:25,485 --> 00:01:27,510
her in that hat,

39
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:29,685
him in the photo

40
00:01:29,835 --> 00:01:31,860
before all that.

41
00:01:32,010 --> 00:01:34,036
Or after that.

42
00:01:34,186 --> 00:01:36,211
Or during. Wait.

43
00:01:36,361 --> 00:01:38,386
Was that before

44
00:01:38,536 --> 00:01:40,561
you changed your name?

45
00:01:40,711 --> 00:01:42,737
I know your face.

46
00:01:42,887 --> 00:01:44,912
I knew your face.

47
00:01:45,062 --> 00:01:47,087
I know it now

48
00:01:47,237 --> 00:01:49,262
in a different way.

49
00:01:49,412 --> 00:01:51,438
They said, “It’s simple.”

50
00:01:51,588 --> 00:01:53,613
I said, “It’s not.”

51
00:01:53,763 --> 00:01:55,788
They said, “Just love them.”

52
00:01:55,938 --> 00:01:57,963
I said, “I do.”

53
00:01:58,113 --> 00:02:00,139
But love’s not the part

54
00:02:00,289 --> 00:02:02,314
that I’m tripping through.

55
00:02:02,464 --> 00:02:04,489
It’s camp in June

56
00:02:04,639 --> 00:02:06,664
and the missing you.

57
00:02:06,814 --> 00:02:08,840
If she’s he and he’s still you,

58
00:02:08,990 --> 00:02:11,015
and you’re still you but the rule says
“who,”

59
00:02:11,165 --> 00:02:13,190
how’s a girls’ camp a girls’ camp

60
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:15,365
when the girls aren’t there?

61
00:02:15,515 --> 00:02:17,541
If we said we’d go like we always do,

62
00:02:17,691 --> 00:02:19,716
and I still mean me and I still mean you,

63
00:02:19,866 --> 00:02:21,891
why’s the same same place

64
00:02:22,041 --> 00:02:24,066
suddenly somewhere?

65
00:02:24,216 --> 00:02:26,242
They can’t come in

66
00:02:26,392 --> 00:02:28,417
because they’re boys now.

67
00:02:28,567 --> 00:02:30,592
I can go back,

68
00:02:30,742 --> 00:02:32,768
but not with them now.

69
00:02:32,918 --> 00:02:34,943
And that’s the part

70
00:02:35,093 --> 00:02:37,118
that no one says plain,

71
00:02:37,268 --> 00:02:39,293
how change can fit

72
00:02:39,443 --> 00:02:41,469
and still rearrange.

73
00:02:41,619 --> 00:02:43,644
So I can get it

74
00:02:43,794 --> 00:02:45,819
and still feel weird.

75
00:02:45,969 --> 00:02:47,994
I can be kind

76
00:02:48,144 --> 00:02:50,170
and still want last year.

77
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:52,345
I can say “him”

78
00:02:52,495 --> 00:02:54,520
and still miss “her,”

79
00:02:54,670 --> 00:02:56,695
not who he is,

80
00:02:56,845 --> 00:02:58,871
just when we were.

81
00:02:59,021 --> 00:03:01,046
If she’s he and he’s still you,

82
00:03:01,196 --> 00:03:03,221
and you’re still you and I know that’s
true,

83
00:03:03,371 --> 00:03:05,396
why does truth make room

84
00:03:05,546 --> 00:03:07,572
and take room too?

85
00:03:07,722 --> 00:03:09,747
If we’re still friends,

86
00:03:09,897 --> 00:03:11,922
and I know we are,

87
00:03:12,072 --> 00:03:14,097
why’s the bunk feel full

88
00:03:14,247 --> 00:03:16,273
and the whole camp far?

89
00:03:16,423 --> 00:03:18,448
If summer comes

90
00:03:18,598 --> 00:03:20,623
and the forms stay same,

91
00:03:20,773 --> 00:03:22,798
can I miss the camp

92
00:03:22,948 --> 00:03:24,974
and still say your name?

93
00:03:25,124 --> 00:03:27,149
I still know you.

94
00:03:27,299 --> 00:03:29,324
I still do.

95
00:03:29,474 --> 00:03:31,499
I just don’t know

96
00:03:31,649 --> 00:03:33,675
what summer does

97
00:03:33,825 --> 00:03:35,850
with that truth.
